# Planning an Env-Var to Typed CLI-Option Migration Across a Fan-Out of Call Sites

(v1.0.0 body: mapped each env-reading helper 1:1 to the reaching options object;
kept the helper module as the single source of DEFAULT CONSTANTS; None-sentinel CLI
flag deferring to the pydantic field default; centralized flags in a shared
add_*_arg(parser); made env-removal a TESTED invariant. Failed-Attempts table framed
six RISKS as "assumptions a plan author makes that are easy to get wrong" --
free-function options reach, per-phase knob consolidation, different-default fold,
line-number drift, surviving library-layer HEPH_GH_CLI_TIMEOUT, under-enumerated
timeout-assertion test blast radius. Full v1.0.0 text retained in git history at
PR #2815.)
